#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:11
msgid "Standard Interface"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:13
msgid ""
"This is the main interface of the application. All the modules are "
"available, but there are limits depending on the profile settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:-1
msgid "GLPI standard interface"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:21
msgid ""
"The home page of the standard interface provides a summary view for quick"
" access to active elements (tickets, notes, planning, contracts, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:23
msgid "It is divided into 5 views:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:25
msgid "*Dashboard*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:27
msgid "A customizable dashboard"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:28
msgid "*Personal view*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:30
msgid ""
"Shows the tickets opened, rejected, to be processed, to be approved (for "
"which the logged-in user is the requestor) or those on which this user "
"has an interaction as a validator or technician (awaiting validation, in "
"progress, to be closed, in waiting). This view also offers him current "
"issues, his schedule and available notes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:31
msgid "*Group view*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:33
msgid ""
"Offers the same information about tickets and issues as the personal "
"view, but using the groups to which it belongs as a reference. Depending "
"on their profile, they may or may not have access to the tickets for "
"which their groups are requesting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:35
msgid "*Global view*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:37
msgid ""
"Offers statistics on tickets and issues according to their status and on "
"contracts according to their expiration date. It also offers the view of "
"the latest additions of objects in GLPI. Depending on the configuration "
"used, new tickets can also be presented in this tab."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:39
msgid "*RSS feed*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:41
msgid ""
"Proposes the content of defined RSS feeds. :doc:`RSS feeds are managed "
"from the \"Tools  > RSS Feeds\" menu <../modules/tools/rssfeed>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:45
msgid "For Personal and Group views, only tables with information are displayed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:49
msgid ""
"Two security messages may be displayed when you log in for the first time"
" after completing the installation procedure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:51
msgid ""
"The first asks you to change the passwords of the accounts created by "
"default in GLPI, the second asks you to delete the directory "
"``glpi/install``. There may also be one or more other messages here "
"related to security or needed database schema changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:-1
msgid "Security messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:59
msgid ""
"As long as you have not performed these operations, the messages will "
"remain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:64
msgid "Simplified Interface"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:66
msgid ""
"It is the most restrictive interface of the application and is built for "
"an end-user more than a technician. Therefore, the number of available "
"modules is reduced to a minimum."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:-1
msgid "GLPI simplified interface"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:73
msgid ""
"It is intended for users with very limited permissions in the application"
" such as the built-in self-service and helpdesk profiles."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:75
msgid ""
"In the default configuration, a user can, from this interface, only "
"create tickets, follow the processing of their tickets, make "
"reservations, view the notes or public RSS feeds (or create private notes"
" or feeds) and consult the Frequently Asked Questions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps/interfaces.rst:77
msgid ""
"The home page offers the number of its tickets according to their status "
"as well as the most popular and recent FAQ topics."
msgstr ""

